  description: Batik Canting is a traditional Javanese art where intricate patterns
    are hand-drawn onto fabric using melted wax. The textile is dyed and then boiled
    to remove the wax, revealing detailed floral, geometric, or  abstract designs.
    This finished material is commonly used to create clothing for both men and women.
